label: Newton Cash Book 1871-1872
description: This book contains records of monetary transactions that took  place on the plantation from February 4th 1871 to August 2nd 1872. It includes records of monies received for rent, from the sale of cattle and other livestock and other goods such as potatoes etc. It also includes monies paid to labourers, carpenters, masons and the engine driver as well as payment for supplies for use on the plantation.
